:INFO
Starting Simple: Traditional Mead
For a one-gallon batch, you need about 1.1 to 1.4 kg of quality honey \
(darker wildflower honeys give more complex flavor), 3.5 liters of water, \
and one packet of wine or mead yeast (Lalvin 71B is a solid first choice). \
No boiling needed. Boiling drives off aroma compounds in the honey.

